    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Frans van Cranevelt (Brussels, 16 September
                    1536)</head>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <p>He was uncertain if he should reply to Frans van Cranevelt’s pleasing
                            poem in verse or prose. He should not be the only one who is silent
                            about losing Erasmus of Rotterdam, so he has poured out his feelings in
                            a poem; it will be van Cranavelt’s task to polish it. 2. The Emperor
                            occupied Arles after they killed every armed fighter who resisted. The
                            exiles from Florence attacked Genoa, but they were repelled. They are
                            hoping that the Emperor will bring peace to Italy. The rest of the news
                            briefly: Péronne is under siege; Damme has capitulated to the Emperor;
                            the fleet has set sail for the British ocean; Cornelis de Schepper and
                            Jean Godschalk went to Zeelandia the day before yesterday; and the
                            Persians are really squeezing the Turks.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p><app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"/>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">Reverendissimi domini</rdg>
                    </app> Nicolai <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Olai</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">Olahi</rdg>
                    </app> ad eundem responsio. </p>
                <p>[1.] Subdubius fui aliquandiu, Ornatissime Craneveldi, an soluta oratione vel
                    numeris, quorum iam a multis annis in desuetudinem <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">venit</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">veni</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">veni</rdg>
                    </app> ad tua carmina, ut meum <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">esse potest</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">est</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">est</rdg>
                    </app> iudicium, non inconcinna responderem. Ne tamen solus viderer in tanti
                        <persName>amici</persName><note type="critic">Erasmus of Rotterdam.</note>
                    mei morte, mihi ob amicitiam nostram mutuam <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">maxima</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">maxime</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">maxime</rdg>
                    </app> certe acerba tacere, et eius fatum non deflere, hos qualescumque numeros
                    inter meas urgentes et molestas aulicas occupationes effudi potius, <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">qua</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">quam</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">quam</rdg>
                    </app> scripsi, quos ad te mitto. Tuum erit eorum ineptias tollere et polire,
                    tandemque ad me remittere litura abunde ornatos. </p>
                <p>[2.] <persName>Caesar</persName>
                    <placeName>Arelato</placeName><note type="critic">Arles.</note> potitus est
                    interfectis, uti dicunt, omnibus eius praesidionariis<note type="critic">‘which
                        serves as a guard’, <hi rend="smallcap">Hoven</hi> 2006, 430.</note>
                    militibus et civibus. Exsules Florentini, conscriptis in Italia pecunia Gallica
                    militibus, aggressi nuper fuere <placeName>Genuam</placeName> duabus ex
                    partibus, sed repulsi magna eorum caede. Spes est caesaris exercitum, qui ad
                    Italiam in <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">parte servanda</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">pace servandam</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">pace servandam</rdg>
                    </app> relictus fuit, eos brevi prostraturum. <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Perona</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">Peronaeque</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">
                            <del corresp="Olahus">Perona</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                                >Peronae</add></rdg>
                    </app><note type="critic">Péronne.</note> obsidio soluta est.<note type="critic"
                        >The siege ended on 11 September, 1536.</note> Et non spero aliquid nobis
                    magnae laudis ex hac nostra expeditione venturum, militibus iam, ut audio, domum
                    redire cupientibus. <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Dani</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">Dammum</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">Dammum</rdg>
                    </app><note type="critic">Damme.</note> oppidum iampridem se <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">dedit</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">dedidit</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">dedidit</rdg>
                    </app> caesari. Nunc expedita fuit classis satis valida ad Oceanum Britannicum,
                    si quid boni nostri facere poterint. Praefecti <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">his</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">huic</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">hinc</rdg>
                    </app> dominus de <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Benuir</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III"><del corresp="Olahus"> Benuir</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">Byren</add></rdg>
                    </app><note type="critic">We do not know him more closely.</note> et <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Brodarod</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">Brodaroc</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III"><del corresp="Olahus">Brodarod</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Bredarod</add></rdg>
                    </app>.<note type="critic">We do not know him more closely.</note> Commissarii
                    dati Cornelius <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Scepperus</del></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                            >Scepperus</add></rdg>
                    </app> et <persName>Gothschalcus</persName><note type="critic">Jean
                        Godschalck.</note> nostri, qui nudiustertius in Zelandiam hinc solverunt.
                    Persae dicuntur <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Turcae</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">Turcis</add> nunc</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">nunc Thurcis</rdg>
                    </app> instare acerrime, cuius rei causa Turcarum caesar praesidionarios suos
                    milites ad se ex finibus Hungariae revocasse dicitur. Nunc tempus esset, si
                    principes <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">Christinae</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Christiani</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III">Christiani</rdg>
                    </app> in recuperanda Hungaria Ferdinando regi nostro adessent. Alia nunc nulla
                    habeo. Bene vale. </p>
                <p><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 16. Septembris 1536. </p>
                <p>[Elegia ad sepulchrum Erasmi Roterodami]<note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 424–426; <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934,
                        34–36; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 346–348.</note></p>
                <p> [Epitaphium eiusdem per eundem]<note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 426; <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 36;
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 349.</note></p>
                <p>[Aliud eiusdem]<note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 427;
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 36–37; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Neagu</hi> 2003, 349.</note></p>
                <p> [Aliud eiusdem]<note type="critic"><hi rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 427;
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 37; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Neagu</hi> 2003,
                    350.</note><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?></p><?oxy_custom_end?>
            </div>
        </body>
